@6000 = ~Sword of Dusk and Dawn +3~
@6001 = ~Sword of Dusk and Dawn +3
Rumored to have been forged by an ancient cult that attempted to unite the godly disciplines of the light and the dark, this exquisitely crafted longsword is a symbol of the eternal cycle between light and shadow and the never-ending struggle between light and shadow that governs the realms. Other folk link its creation to priests of Selune and Shar attempting to coax the deities into a truce, perhaps making this sword a symbol of this communion, while others claim that it represents the balance between evil and good, but none can confirm any such claims.

The blade itself shifts its appearance and powers with the rise and fall of the sun. During the night, the sword ignites with an inner fire, glowing faintly as if bathed in the final embers of the setting sun. With each strike, it delivers searing flames to its foes, a burning reminder to nocturnal creatures that they are not truly safe from the light and burn of the stars.

As the sun rises, the sword transforms, its fiery glow dimming as a cold, frosty aura begins to emanate from the blade. In the daylight hours, each swing deals cold damage, representing the inevitable approach of the chill of night. Even under the bright sun, the chill of twilight lurks, reminding all who face the sword that darkness will return, and none can escape its creeping grasp.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– +25% resistance to fire and cold

Charge abilities:
– Earthly Reminder, two times per day
  Special: At night, spell acts as a Sunfire that blinds for 3 rounds and deals 8d6 fire damage plus 10 extra against the undead. During the day, it deals 8d6 cold damage and inflicts Slow for 3 rounds
  Area of effect: Every non-allied creature in a 15 ft. radius around the wielder

THAC0: +3
Damage: 1d8+3, +1d6 fire/magic damage (during the night), +1d6 cold/magic damage (during the day)
Damage type: Slashing
Speed Factor: 2
Proficiency Type: Long Sword
Type: One-handed
Requires:
 6 Strength

Weight: 4~


@6010 = ~This silver sword is carried by some followers of the Lady of Dreams, also known as The Lunar Lady, and Sehanine Moonbow, who is arguably the most powerful member of the Seldarine. Sleep and dreams are an intrinsic part of the goddess' portfolio, to the point where even just looking at her could put anyone to sleep.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Immunity to sleep and unconsciousness
– +1 bonus to saving throws against Illusion and Enchantment effects

Combat abilities:
– Hit target must save vs. Spell or fall asleep for 1 round
– Effective vs. werewolves and other lycanthropes resistant to normal weapons

Charge abilities:
– Mists of Slumber once per day
  Special: All enemies in the area must save vs. Spell at -2 or fall asleep for 3 rounds. This effect cannot be dispelled, but enemies will wake up if attacked
  Duration: The mist lasts for 5 rounds
  Area of effect: Every enemy in a 15 ft. radius around the wielder

THAC0: +3
Damage: 1d8+2, +1d2 magic damage
Damage type: Slashing
Speed Factor: 3
Proficiency Type: Long Sword
Type: One-handed
Requires:
 5 Strength

Weight: 2~

@6020 = ~Estoc~
@6021 = ~Estocs are the largest of the thrusting swords, renowned for being capable of piercing an armored knight in one thrust. Despite their large size, they can be wielded rather nimbly, leaving little opportunity for the enemy to counter. Much like their smaller counterparts, estocs are +5% more likely to critically hit than other weapons of their category.

STATISTICS:

Damage: 1d8+1 (piercing or slashing)
Speed Factor: 6
Proficiency Type: Long Sword / Estoc
Type: Two-handed
Requires:
 10 Strength
 14 Dexterity

Weight: 2~

@6030 = ~Guiding Moonlight~
@6031 = ~The blade of this greatsword shines like the brilliant rays of the moon with a celestial grace. Its blade is etched with tiny delicate runes depicting the phases of the moon. It is said that the blade was born during a rare lunar convergence, when Selûne bestowed a sliver of her divine light upon the mortal realm. The weapon's presence offers guidance in times of uncertainty, inspiring its bearer to rise against the encroaching shadows.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– +20% Cold Resistance (+40% during the night)
– +15% Magic Resistance (+30% during the night)
– +10% Magic Damage Resistance (+20% during the night)
– +10 Lore
– Sets automatically one point in the Two-Handed Swords proficiency (unless higher)
– May be used by wizards and sorcerers, including multi-classed wizards
– Wizards and sorcerers use this weapon at a Speed Factor of 0

Combat abilities:
Extra magic damage based on the wielder's Intelligence score:
 – 10-11: +1
 – 12-13: +2
 – 14-15: 1d2+2
 – 16-17: 1d3+3
 – 18-19: 1d4+4
 – 20-21: 1d5+5
 – 22-23: 1d6+6
 – 24: 1d7+7
 – 25: 1d8+8

Charge abilities:
– Moonlight Bolt, once per day
  Special: Fires a bolt of moonlight at the target, causing 6d6 magic damage, disabling their Magic Resistance, and increasing their susceptibility to magic damage by 25% for 2 rounds. No save is allowed
  Range: 60 ft.
  Area of Effect: 1 creature

THAC0: +3
Damage: 1d10, or 1d10+3 for arcane casters
Damage type: Slashing
Speed Factor: 7
Proficiency Type: Two-handed Sword
Type: Two-handed
Requires:
 14 Strength
 10 Intelligence

Weight: 15~

@6040 = ~Storm's Monarch +3~
@6041 = ~This estoc channels the fury of the storm and the power of lightning. Some people speculate this blade was crafted during the Time of Troubles, when gods walked among mortals, maybe by Talos himself, but such rumors are impossible to confirm and might not be more than hearsay. Nevertheless, the destructive power of the blade is undeniable.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– +40% resistance to electricity

Combat abilities:
– Each hit decreases the target's resistance to electricity by 5% for 2 rounds

Charge abilities:
– Blink Bolt, once per day
  Special: Instantly teleport into melee range of the target, causing an electric shock that deals 8d4 electric damage and stuns the target for 1 round if a save vs. Death at -4 is failed. The shock then pulses outward, chaining to all enemies around, dealing 4d4 electric damage. For one round after this, the caster will cause 100% more electric damage and become Hasted.
  Range: 60 ft.
  Area of Effect: 1 creature

THAC0: +3
Damage: 1d8+4, 1d4+1 electric damage
Damage type: Piercing or slashing
Speed Factor: 2
Proficiency Type: Long Sword / Estoc
Type: Two-handed
Requires:
 10 Strength
 14 Dexterity

Weight: 2~

// nwn/nwn2 inspired
@8000 = ~Lawgiver +1~
@8001 = ~The bane of the chaotic or morally suspect, a Lawgiver blade has but one purpose: to enforce the rule of law wherever that authority is challenged or questioned. Whether or not the concept of "law" coincides with the concept of "justice" is largely irrelevant, as the owners of these weapons often view the world in a very polarized fashion. There is right and there is wrong, and other details only serve to confuse the matter.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– +2 bonus to saving throws and AC vs. chaotically-aligned enemies

Combat abilities:
– Acts as +3 weapon vs. chaotically-aligned enemies for the purposes of overcoming weapon immunities

THAC0: +1, +3 vs. chaotically-aligned enemies
Damage: 2d4+1, +1d4 vs. chaotically-aligned enemies
Damage type: Slashing
Speed Factor: 7
Proficiency Type: Bastard Sword
Type: One-handed
Requires:
 11 Strength

Weight: 10~

@8002 = ~The Left Hand~
@8003 = ~The Night Thief was a vicious assassin who specialized in fighting with two daggers. This knife was the weaker of the two items, but it granted him greater abilities in combat. One merchant in Sembia discovered these abilities when he laid an ambush for the assassin. He found all twelve of his guards dead and the lure, a two pound diamond, gone.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– AC: +2
– Can dual-wield more effectively depending on the wielder's existing ability:
  – Zero or one proficiency points: Two points are granted
  – Two proficiency points: Three points are granted
  – Three proficiency points: Off-hand attacks are no longer made with a penalty (perfect dual-wielding)

THAC0: +1
Damage: 1d4+1 (piercing)
Speed Factor: 1
Proficiency Type: Dagger
Type: One-handed
Requires:
 3 Strength

Weight: 1~

@8004 = ~Master Li's Way~
@8005 = ~Once thought a unique instance of the swordmaker's craft, several katanas of this type have now been linked to a ship that ran aground on the Sword Coast some years ago. All bear the markings of Master Hu Li, a great artificer from the east, but little else is known of him.

